TEM images of AgNPrs/I-, in the presence and absence of 6-MP confirm these assertions (Fig. 3
                        ). Furthermore, the fluorescence emission intensity of N, P-CDs decreased by adding AgNPrs/I- (Fig. 4
                        ) because of the spectral overlap between fluorescence emission of N,P-CDs and LSPR band of etched AgNPrs (Fig. S2. ESI). However, in the presence of 6-MP, the fluorescence intensity of N,P-CDs restored (Fig. 4). It can be attributed to the protecting effect of 6-MP on the AgNPrs which resulted in a red-shift in the LSPR peak and the redaction of spectral overlap between N, P-CDs and AgNPrs/I-. We observed that in the presence of 6-MP not only the wavelength shift in LSPR peak of AgNPrs/I- but also the fluorescence recovery of N, P-CDs/AgNPrs/I- was proportional to the concentration of 6-MP. Based on these facts, we designed a dual colorimetric and fluorometric sensor based on N, P-CDs and AgNPrs for the determination of 6-MP.
